				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{{{{{{\mathcal{G}}}}}}}}$$\end{document} symmetrizes the local PES by adding effective training samples (shown as grey circles) while T\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{{{{{{\mathcal{T}}}}}}}}$$\end{document} delocalises the effective sampling over the whole supercell. Then, by considering the full symmetry group F\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
